  "why": "While the paper goes beyond merely reporting failures by correlating erroneous behaviors (WER) with internal state‐coverage (Jaccard index) and defining ‘major function’ vs. ‘corner‐case’ regions, this analysis remains at the level of characterizing where failures occur rather than explaining why the model is vulnerable in those regions (e.g., due to biased or insufficient training data, reliance on spurious features, or overfitting). The work establishes that inputs driving the RNN into unseen abstract states produce more errors, but does not diagnose the underlying causes within the model’s learning or data distribution that give rise to these corner‐case failures.",
